article.story: BOSTON -- — Kino Lilly Jr.'s 19 points helped Brown defeat Harvard 74-72 on Monday. Nana Owusu-Anane made two free throws with 17 seconds left to give Brown a 74-69 lead. Lilly shot 7 for 18, including 4 for 11 from beyond the arc for the Bears (5-12, 1-1 Ivy League). Owusu-Anane scored 18 points while going 7 of 11 and 4 of 4 from the free throw line, and added nine rebounds and three blocks. Felix Kloman was 4 of 7 shooting (3 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. Chisom Okpara led the Crimson (9-6, 0-2) in scoring, finishing with 20 points. Harvard also got 18 points, seven rebounds, five assists and four steals from Malik Mack. Thomas Batties II also had 15 points and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
